    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Headdresses worn by Hopi young women and girls during the Butterfly Dance. Usually made of wood and decorated in vivid colors with designs representative of the wearer's clan and sometimes their dance partner's clan. Can also be seen carved on katsinam.</Note_Text>
